y checks balances but not the actual return of the borrowed tokens.","paths":["Call flashBorrow with malicious target that doesn't return funds properly"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Hardcoded Critical Addresses Create Single Points of Failure","locations":["0xfb772316a54dcd439964b561fc2c173697aeeb5b/Contract.sol:899-903"],"claim":"Critical protocol addresses (bZxContract, wethToken, gasToken, arbitraryCaller) are hardcoded and cannot be changed, creating single points of failure.","impact":"If any of these hardcoded addresses are compromised, deprecated, or have issues, the entire protocol could be affected with no ability to update the addresses.","paths":["If hardcoded address is compromised or deprecated, no recovery mechanism exists"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"LowerAdmin Role Has Full Control Without Timelock","locations":["0xfb772316a54dcd439964b561fc2c173697aeeb5b/Contract.sol:2176-2185"],"claim":"The updateSettings function allows a lowerAdmin (stored in storage slot) to execute arbitrary calls on the contract. There is no timelock or multi-sig requirement for this powerful privilege.","impact":"The lowerAdmin can immediately execute arbitrary code to steal funds or modify contract state with no delay or governance oversight.","paths":["If lowerAdmin address is compromised, attacker can drain all funds via updateSettings"]},{"id":"F-006","severity":"Medium","confidence":"medium","title":"Missing Return Value Check on Token Transfer in burn","locations":["0xfb772316a54dcd439964b561fc2c173697aeeb5b/Contract.sol:948-951"],"claim":"The burn function transfers loan tokens to the receiver using _safeTransfer but doesn't check the return value of the transfer, potentially allowing tokens to get stuck if the transfer fails silently.","impact":"If the token transfer fails (e.g., due to contract pause), the function continues without proper error handling, potentially causing accounting discrepancies.","paths":["Token contract returns false on transfer during burn"]},{"id":"F-007","severity":"Medium","confidence":"low","title":"Oracle Price Feed Dependency Without Validation","locations":["0xfb772316a54dcd439964b561fc2c173697aeeb5b/Contract.sol:1721-1728"],"claim":"The _totalDeposit function queries price feeds from the bZx protocol without additional validation or circuit breakers for extreme price values.","impact":"If the price feed returns manipulated or extreme values, it could cause incorrect collateral calculations leading to undercollateralized loans or liquidations.","paths":["Manipulate oracle price to cause incorrect loan calculations"]},{"id":"F-008","severity":"Low","confidence":"medium","title":"Floating Pragma Solidity Version","locations":["0x7f3fe9d492a9a60aebb06d82cba23c6f32cad10b/Contract.sol:6","0xfb772316a54dcd439964b561fc2c173697aeeb5b/Contract.sol:6"],"claim":"Both contracts use 'pragma solidity 0.5.17' which locks to a specific version, but the code may behave differently in other 0.5.x versions due to EVM changes.","impact":"Future compiler versions may have different behavior or security implications. This is informational for future compatibility.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-009","severity":"Low","confidence":"low","title":"Insufficient Event Emissions for Sensitive Operations","locations":["0xfb772316a54dcd439964b561fc2c173697aeeb5b/Contract.sol:2172-2206"],"claim":"The updateSettings function executes arbitrary calls but doesn't emit events for the executed operations, making it difficult to track admin actions on-chain.","impact":"Lack of visibility into admin actions could delay detection of malicious behavior.","paths":[]},{"id":"F-010","severity":"Informational","confidence":"high","title":"IERC20 Interface Missing Return Value for transfer/transferFrom","locations":["0xfb772316a54dcd439964b561fc2c173697aeeb5b/Contract.sol:15-27","0x7f3fe9d492a9a60aebb06d82cba23c6f32cad10b/Contract.sol:14-26"],"claim":"The IERC20 interface defines transfer and transferFrom as returning bool but doesn't enforce that implementation contracts return true on success, which could lead to silent failures with some tokens.","impact":"Some tokens (like USDT) don't return boolean on transfer functions. The _safeTransfer helper does check return values, providing some protection, but the interface design is incomplete.","paths":[]}]
