/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:7:### F-002: Minting trusts the requested ERC20 deposit amount instead of the amount actually received
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:11:The mint path prices shares from the caller-supplied `depositAmount` before any transfer happens, then only checks whether `transferFrom` returned success. It never measures the contract's actual balance delta, so a fee-on-transfer or otherwise deflationary `loanTokenAddress` can deliver fewer tokens than `depositAmount` while the minter still receives shares as if the full amount arrived.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:13:**Impact:** An attacker can over-mint iTokens, diluting existing lenders and later redeeming more underlying than they contributed. If enough liquidity exists, this can make the pool insolvent.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:17:- Use a pool whose `loanTokenAddress` burns, taxes, or otherwise transfers less than the requested amount.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:21:- Receive shares computed from `X`, then burn them later for a disproportionate amount of underlying.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:27:### F-003: Borrow and margin-trade accounting can overstate user deposits for fee-on-transfer tokens
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:53:When `totalSupply_ == 0`, `_totalAssetSupply` returns zero and `_tokenPrice` falls back to `initialPrice`, ignoring any underlying tokens already sitting in the pool. If the contract is pre-funded or receives stray underlying before the first mint, the first supplier can buy shares at the default price instead of paying for the pre-existing assets.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:55:**Impact:** Any bootstrap liquidity or accidental direct transfer of underlying into an uninitialized pool can be stolen by the first minter.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:59:- Transfer underlying tokens into the pool before any iTokens exist.
/Users/zhanglongqin/AuditHoundV2/output/bzx2_p5_125_end/final_report.md:63:- Burn the received iTokens to redeem a disproportionate share of the pre-seeded underlying, including the assets that were already in the pool.
